text: Henk van Essen (5 February 1909 - 23 December 1968) was a Dutch swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1909 births Category:1968 deaths Category:Dutch male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of the Netherlands Category:Swimmers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Swimmers from Amsterdam
